# WHAT IT IS
#   `mautrix-slack` is a **puppeting bridge** — a server-side daemon
#   that, given a Slack workspace's user-level OAuth tokens and a
#   Matrix Appservice registration, creates a virtual Matrix user
#   ("puppet") for every Slack member, a virtual Matrix room
#   ("portal") for every Slack channel and DM, and bidirectionally
#   syncs messages, reactions, edits, deletions, threads, files,
#   typing notifications, read receipts, presence, and call events
#   between the two networks.
#
#   The bridge runs as a long-lived daemon registered with the Matrix
#   homeserver via an Appservice registration file (`registration.yaml`
#   by default).  All bridge-state (which Matrix user is logged into
#   which Slack workspace, which Slack channels are bridged to which
#   Matrix rooms, the in-flight reaction / message ID mappings, the
#   per-user encryption keys) lives in a PostgreSQL database
#   referenced by the config file (`config.yaml` by default).
#
#   `mautrix-slack` is part of the **`bridgev2` generation** of
#   mautrix bridges (rewritten in 2024 onto the unified `bridgev2`
#   abstraction in mautrix-go).  This means it shares its **entire
#   CLI surface** with every other bridgev2-based mautrix bridge:
#   mautrix-discord, mautrix-whatsapp, mautrix-signal, mautrix-
#   telegram, mautrix-twitter, mautrix-meta (Instagram + Facebook
#   Messenger), mautrix-gmessages (Google Messages), mautrix-
#   imessage, mautrix-linkedin, mautrix-googlechat all expose
#   identical CLI flags via the shared `mxmain.BridgeMain` helper
#   from `maunium.net/go/mautrix/bridgev2/matrix/mxmain` — so this
#   completion file is the **reference pattern for every bridgev2-
#   based mautrix bridge** even though it explicitly targets the
#   Slack bridge binary.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from `maunium.net/go/mautrix/
#                       bridgev2/matrix/mxmain/main.go`
#                       `flag.MakeFull(short, long, usage, default)`
#                       declarations + the `cmd/mautrix-slack/main.go`
#                       `BridgeMain` instance; extracted via
#                       raw.githubusercontent.com fetch of both)
#
#   mautrix-slack [-hgvn] [-c <PATH>] [-r <PATH>] [LONG OPTIONS]
#
#   Options:
#     -h, --help                     Show help and exit
#     -v, --version                  Show bridge version and exit
#     --version-json                 Print a JSON object representing
#                                    the bridge version and exit
#                                    (includes os/arch + the embedded
#                                    mautrix-go SDK version + the
#                                    bridge's own version + git
#                                    commit + build time)
#
#     -c, --config <PATH>            Path to config file
#                                    [default: config.yaml]
#                                    (use `-` for stdin)
#     -e, --generate-example-config  Save the example config to the
#                                    config path and quit
#                                    (refuses to overwrite an
#                                    existing file unless `-c -` is
#                                    given to write to stdout)
#     -n, --no-update                Don't save updated config to disk
#                                    (config-version-upgrade migrations
#                                    run in memory only)
#
#     -r, --registration <PATH>      Path where to save the Matrix
#                                    Appservice registration
#                                    [default: registration.yaml]
#     -g, --generate-registration    Generate registration YAML for
#                                    `homeserver.appservices` and
#                                    quit (refuses `--no-update`
#                                    + this flag combination since
#                                    the generated as_token /
#                                    hs_token must be persisted to
#                                    the config file too)
#
#     --ignore-unsupported-database  Run even if the database schema
#                                    is too new (forward-compat
#                                    override)
#     --ignore-foreign-tables        Run even if the database
#                                    contains tables from other
#                                    programs (e.g. tables left
#                                    over from a Synapse-shared
#                                    DB)
#     --ignore-unsupported-server    Run even if the Matrix
#                                    homeserver advertises a
#                                    Client-Server API version
#                                    older than mautrix-go's
#                                    minimum supported version
#
